{"author":{"id":"8e1777f58c0cfe5478428be8f9fcbfe90d25e44689578335da8fc2246fe0915a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1642956451,"nonce":"nJwN2RgzIGXF+2SLXjncMdswMMM=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s48xK_m","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4339#issuecomment-1019523046"},"message":"This idea is really just about a static website, no storage of tools etc. Experience has shown that we don't have the capacity for a new TS and that this is a much larger project than generating a static website imho, which can be also tweaked by subcommunities. I would not mind if this evolves into TS 2.0 with GitHub based artefacts and the GitHub registry, but for the time being I think a small website could already bring us a good step forwards. And this task is so independent of Galaxy code that it could be done by a new contributor or a student imho. If we stay with a Vue based framework we can hopefully also reuse components in the future.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1642956712,"nonce":"hNbdsA12VTR7QoDV+R3IgsWocXo=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOAW4Y0s48xK_mziBW6hs"},"target":"cb992b428660773edfdd669187dd81f4899bae9572eca2bb0d430fc268f1fefb","message":"Thanks, Nicola.\nThis idea is really just about a static website, no storage of tools etc. Experience has shown that we don't have the capacity for a new TS and that this is a much larger project than generating a static website imho. I have sometimes the feeling that as soon as we talk about TS, the entire discussion is dead ;) I would not mind if this evolves into TS 2.0 with GitHub based artifacts and the GitHub registry, but for the time being, I think a small website could already bring us a good step forwards. And this task is so independent of Galaxy code that it could be done by a new contributor or a student imho. If we stay with a Vue-based framework we can hopefully also reuse components in the future.","files":null}]}